# usbtrace

eBPF-based USB subsystem tracer & diagnostic tool for Linux BSP. Inspired by
nettrace (tracks USB device lifecycle/URBs/power/class-traffic instead of skb).
Built on libbpf + CO-RE; portable across kernels and x86/x86_64/arm/arm64.

## Non-negotiable principles

1. **Modular**: every capability is a self-contained module under
   `src/modules/<name>/` (own `.bpf.c` + `.c` + `.h`). Adding a module must NOT
   require editing core (`src/main.c`, `src/module.c`) or the Makefile.
2. **CO-RE always**: in BPF code, access kernel structs only via
   `BPF_CORE_READ(...)`. Never hardcode struct offsets. One source, all arches.
3. **Portable arch**: never assume x86. `-D__TARGET_ARCH_$(ARCH)` is the only
   arch knob; keep kprobe arg access via `BPF_KPROBE`/`PT_REGS_*` macros.
4. **Vendored toolchain**: libbpf (v1.5.0) and bpftool are git submodules under
   `third_party/`. Do not switch to system libbpf.

## Layout

- `src/main.c` ‚Äî CLI: global opts + subcommand dispatch (`list`/`help`/<module>).
- `src/module.c` + `include/usbtrace/module.h` ‚Äî module registry (self-register
  via `USBTRACE_MODULE_REGISTER`, constructor-based linked list).
- `include/usbtrace/common.h` ‚Äî BPF-safe shared types; every ring-buffer record
  starts with `struct usbtrace_event_hdr { kind; size; ts_ns; }`.
- `src/run.c` + `include/usbtrace/run.h` ‚Äî shared `usbtrace_run()` harness
  (feature-probe‚Üíload‚Üíattach‚Üíring buffer‚Üípoll‚Üíteardown); every single-skeleton
  module uses it.
- `src/probe.c` + `include/usbtrace/probe.h` ‚Äî `usbtrace_autoload_filter()`:
  per-program graceful degradation (disables hooks whose target is absent on this
  kernel so one missing function doesn't sink the module). Auto-run by the
  harness; `diag` calls it before its manual `__load`.
- `include/usbtrace/class.h` + `class_*` + `src/class_stream.c` ‚Äî class-traffic
  foundation shared by uvc/uac/hid/storage (one `class_urb_event`); feeds `diag`.
- `src/modules/urb/` ‚Äî reference tracing module; `src/modules/uvc/` ‚Äî reference
  class module; `src/modules/diag/` ‚Äî cross-module rule engine.
- `docs/` ‚Äî architecture, modules, class, diag, roadmap, build. Keep updated.

## Conventions

- License: GPL-2.0; every `.bpf.c` needs `char LICENSE[] SEC("license") = "GPL";`.
- Events go through one `BPF_MAP_TYPE_RINGBUF` named `events`; route by `hdr.kind`.
- Module `run()` opens its skeleton + sets `.rodata` cfg, then calls
  `usbtrace_run()`; it never hand-rolls the load/attach/poll loop.
- Tunables: `const volatile struct <name>_config cfg = {};` (`= {}` needed for
  clang ‚â§10 BTF). `libbpf_set_print()` is done once in `main.c`.
- Run requires root + kernel BTF (`/sys/kernel/btf/vmlinux`).
- Build: `make deps` once, then `make`. See `usbtrace-build` rule for cross.
